Ad Text:
Kinexus is a recruitment agency specialising in security-cleared positions across the Defence industry. We place contractors into assignments with our clients to support niche skillsets, assist with surges on key projects, and provide specialised expertise that is hard to find elsewhere.

Contract opportunities have been more limited recently, following a challenging few years in the industry. Despite this, we continue to see strong demand for several specialised skillsets, and we expect this to carry into the new year.

Looking ahead to 2026, Melbourne's hiring will focus on Maritime and Land projects, with communications and autonomous projects continuing to offer opportunities for top talent.

Because of this, we're looking to connect with Defence professionals who hold these in-demand skills, which we see as critical to Defence contracting.

Skillsets include:

Systems Engineers - Combat, Electrical, Comms, V&V
Systems Safety Engineers
Test Engineers
ILS Engineers
Drafters - Mechanical, Electrical
Software Engineers - C++, Java, AI/ML
Project Controls / Project Schedulers - OPP, P6
Procurement/Commercial specialists

If you'll be looking for a new contract in 2026, or want to learn more about the market, rates, and the projects driving hiring in Melbourne, please apply today.

Please note: candidates should hold a current Defence security clearance (Baseline minimum; NV1 preferred) and have prior experience working on Defence programs.

All applications should include your resume as a word document.

For more information, visit our website, www.kinexus.com.au or contact Ellen Hanratty on 03 9982 0303.

Senior Consultant - Data Engineering

Are you a seasoned data engineering professional who excels in developing data-driven solutions? Do you have a passion for leading transformational initiatives that deliver measurable business success? If solving complex challenges and driving innovative outcomes excites you, Synogize wants to meet you!

We’re seeking a Senior Consultant with a deep understanding of Data Engineering to join our dynamic team in Melbourne. To be considered, candidates must have full, permanent working rights in Australia and at least 5+ years of industry experience in Data Engineering.

About You

You are someone who:

Collaborates closely with clients, designing tailored analytics strategies to solve complex business challenges.
Leads technical problem-solving efforts, optimizing data to deliver impactful insights.
Transforms business needs into actionable data models that drive strategic decision-making.
Is excited by the opportunity to mentor junior team members and play a key role in company growth.
Delivers outstanding client results with tangible business value.
Is dedicated to continuous improvement and keeps up with the latest tools and trends in data analytics.

Key Responsibilities

Data Modeling & Architecture: Design, build, and maintain scalable data models that meet both client and internal needs.
ETL Development: Oversee the development of robust ETL/ELT pipelines, transforming raw data into structured, analyzable datasets.
Data Transformation: Lead SQL-based transformations using tools like dbt and Coalesce, delivering clean datasets for analysis.
Analytics Solutions: Integrate and manage analytics platforms (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, Looker) with data sources, working closely with BI and data teams.
Data Quality & Governance: Implement data governance frameworks to ensure data accuracy and integrity.
Client Leadership: Guide clients through technical challenges and deliver high-impact solutions that meet business goals.
Cross-functional Collaboration: Work with data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders to drive data-driven decision-making.
Performance Optimization: Monitor and improve the scalability and performance of data models and pipelines.

Required Skills & Experience

Advanced SQL expertise (5+ years) with strong experience in complex queries, stored procedures, and managing large datasets.
Hands-on experience with cloud platforms like Snowflake, BigQuery, Fabric, or Databricks.
Mastery of ETL/ELT processes and modern data transformation tools (e.g., dbt, Coalesce).
Expertise in creating compelling data visualizations using tools like Tableau, Power BI, or Looker.
Excellent communication skills, capable of explaining complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
Proven ability to deliver real-time analytics solutions in dynamic environments.

Bonus Skills

Machine learning or advanced data science techniques.
Passion for data storytelling and creating engaging visualizations.
Experience in data governance and ensuring data security, quality, and accuracy.

Required Qualifications

Must hold a valid permanent work visa, permanent residency, or Australian citizenship.
Bachelor's or Graduate's Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering, Applied math, Statistics, Physics, or equivalent experience.

About Synogize

At Synogize, we harness synergy and passion to drive success. Founded by Data & Analytics professionals, we pride ourselves on bridging the gap between people, processes, and technology to deliver innovative solutions. Our mission is to create transformative outcomes by aligning data, technology, and talent, helping organizations shape the future of innovation.

Next Steps

If this opportunity excites you, we’d love to hear from you! Please apply by submitting your resume.

Note to Recruitment Agencies: We have this role covered and do not accept unsolicited CVs. We are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. Thank you.

Senior Network Automation Engineer

Leading Government client (consulting through FinXL)

FinXL Professional Services is a leading IT consultancy that partners with clients to bridge the gap between business needs and technology capabilities. Since 2003, we've been delivering high-value ICT services across government, finance, telecommunications, and enterprise sectors.

FinXL is seeking a Senior Network Automation Engineer to join our consulting team and be deployed with a leading Government client on a key transformation engagement. FinXL is also able to take over existing visas and provide sponsorship for consultants.

Responsibilities

Design canonical role/subnet/service object models for ASA/CSM and ACI/APIC

Validate and sign off candidate rules; lead passive and canary deployments

Produce runbooks, emergency rollback procedures, and change control artefacts

Mentor automation engineers on APIC payloads and CSM job design

Monitor post-deploy telemetry and authorise reverts when SLA thresholds exceed

Configure and manage F5 GTM and LTM for application traffic distribution

Develop and maintain network automation scripts and workflows using Python and Terraform

Key Skills & Experience

Deep experience with Cisco ASA, Cisco ACI and APIC REST/API models

Proven design and execution of enterprise firewall policy rollouts

Strong troubleshooting and capacity planning skills

Hands-on experience with F5 GTM (Global Traffic Manager) and LTM

Proficiency in network automation using Python and Terraform

CCNP/CCIE or equivalent certification

Experience with CI/CD pipelines for network automation

Why Join FinXL?

Work on a high-impact, large-scale network transformation program.

Technical leadership role shaping complex migration designs.

Hands-on automation with Python, Terraform, ACI, and F5.


Next Steps

If you would like to apply for this opportunity, please submit your CV via SEEK.

Please note that due to the volume of responses, only shortlisted consultants will be contacted.

At Medibank, we believe our greatest potential lies in the people who work with us. We're driven by a simple purpose: to create the best health and wellbeing for all Australians. Our Data & Technology team plays a vital role in making that happen.

The Opportunity - Data Engineer / Developer for Data Science Squad

Medibank's Data Hub team has an immediate need for a Data Engineer contractor to support the Data Science Squad. This is a 6-month contract engagement, with a strong possibility of extension.

Daily Rate: $680 per day

The goal is to manage Data Scientist data requirements. To achieve this, we need a skilled Data Engineer to:

Ingest data from multiple systems
Collate, clean, and manipulate the data
Prepare data objects aligned to the Data Science team requirements
Optimize data processing and identify bottlenecks in data processing


This is a hands-on role requiring deep technical expertise and the ability to work independently while collaborating closely with stakeholders.

Key Responsibilities
Design and implement ETL pipelines and data integration solutions
Ingest and transform data from diverse systems for Data Science Squad
Collaborate with the Data Science team to understand data requirements including recommendations on the best approach
Develop and maintain Propensity Models for production
Deploy, monitor, and manage machine learning (ML) models
Maintain high standards of data governance and quality
Support the Data Hub's broader initiatives and compliance obligations

About You

You're a seasoned Data Engineer with a strong background in cloud technologies and enterprise data management. You're confident working with complex datasets and have experience delivering similar compliance or regulatory reporting projects.

Must-Have Skills & Experience:

5+ years in data engineering or enterprise data roles
Strong experience with AWS, SQL, and Python
Experience with MLOps
Experience with SageMaker, model scoring, real-time batch monitoring
Proven ability to ingest and manipulate data from multiple sources
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills

Imagine Working With Us



We know that happy, healthy people make great teams. That's why we're reinventing work—offering flexibility, connection, and wellbeing as part of your everyday experience.

Learn more about our benefits: Medibank Careers - Rewards & Benefits


Inclusion and Accessibility

We're committed to building an inclusive workplace that reflects the diversity of our community. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with disabilities, and members of the LGBTQIA+ community.

Need adjustments or alternative formats during the recruitment process? Contact us at: contractorengagement@medibank.com.au

Ad Text:
Employment Type: Full-Time (35 hours p/week)
Duration: Continuing
Remuneration: Level 9: $148,012 - $157,055 + 17% Super + Leave Loading
Location: UNSW Kensington Campus

About UNSW:
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community, a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

Why Your Role Matters:
UNSW IT is part of UNSW’s Division of Operations and provides high quality, sustainable, flexible products and state of the art services to UNSW. Our priorities are to drive innovative architectures that enable UNSW’s digital future and be a trusted partner of the University.

The Senior Data Engineer is responsible for building, implementing, and supporting data solutions and integration components using data technology components. This role combines expertise in data engineering, data modeling, Master Data Management (MDM), and DevOps practices to ensure efficient data pipelines, reliable deployments, and optimal performance of data systems.

The position reports to the Lead Solution Architect - MDM and Data and has no direct reports.

Responsibilities Include:

Lead the design, development, and implementation of Master Data Management (MDM) solutions, canonical data models, data pipelines, and integrations with business applications.
Drive continuous improvement and scalability of MDM and data platform components aligned with UNSW’s Microsoft-based integration framework and industry best practice.
Provide expert technical leadership and support, guiding developers, vendors, and internal teams to deliver high-quality, integrated solutions.
Design and implement database schemas, ingestion and transformation pipelines, and SQL queries within the Microsoft Azure environment.
Collaborate with architects, engineers, and stakeholders to ensure data solutions meet functional, technical, and business requirements.
Manage project risks, issues, and dependencies to ensure successful outcomes and platform stability.
Support leadership in optimising integration and data services practices, resourcing, and stakeholder engagement across UNSW IT.

For more information regarding the responsibilities for this role, please refer to the Position Description at JOBS@UNSW.

Skills and Experience Summary:

Tertiary qualifications in IT or a related discipline, with 7+ years’ experience in software development and data engineering using cloud architectures and middleware.
Extensive experience with enterprise Master Data Management (MDM) platforms, data modelling, integration, and data design, including SQL queries and database schemas.
Hands-on expertise with Informatica Cloud MDM / Customer 360 / Product 360, including match and merge rules, survivorship logic, hierarchies, workflows, and Golden Record creation.
Proven proficiency in designing and implementing solutions using Azure data services (MS SQL, Synapse, Data Factory, Databricks, Data Lake, Storage Accounts, Service Bus).
Strong experience in data integration using synchronous and asynchronous patterns (API, ESB, ETL) and ETL/ELT tools such as Informatica PowerCenter, IDMC, and Azure Data Factory.
Demonstrated experience developing data solutions to support API integrations, with strong understanding of application, data, and API security and privacy controls.
Proficiency with Azure DevOps and CI/CD tools for automated testing, deployment, and database schema management.
Experience managing data products across the full product lifecycle, with strong product management and stakeholder engagement skills.
Knowledge of system integration methods, development lifecycles, and tools such as Terraform, Ansible, Docker, Kubernetes, Databricks, Artifactory, Git, Jira, and Confluence.
Familiarity with Agile methodologies, including participation in storyboarding, estimation, and project management activities.



Benefits and Culture: People are at the core of everything we do. We recognise it is the contributions of our staff who make UNSW one of the best universities in Australia and the world.  Our benefits include: 

Career development opportunities 
17% Superannuation contributions
Generous leave entitlements including an additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period 
Staff Discounts (retail, education, fitness and more)
Salary sacrificing & novated leasing available



How to Apply: Make each day matter with a meaningful career at UNSW. Submit your CV via the application portal before 9am on December 1st, 2025.

A copy of the Position Description can be found on JOBS@UNSW.

Get in Touch: For queries regarding the recruitment process, contact Lucy Gerondis, Talent Acquisition Consultant, UNSW: l.gerondis@unsw.edu.au
Applications sent via email will not be accepted, please apply via the application portal.

UNSW is committed to evolving a culture that embraces equity and supports a diverse and inclusive community where everyone can participate fairly, in a safe and respectful environment. We welcome candidates from all backgrounds and encourage applications from people of diverse gender, sexual orientation, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander background, people with disability and those with caring and family responsibilities. UNSW provides workplace adjustments for people with disability, and access to flexible work options for eligible staff.

The University reserves the right not to proceed with any appointment.

Our Client is looking for an experienced IT Solution Designer to lead the design and implementation of an automated change management solution built on ServiceNow DevOps Change Velocity and Azure DevOps.

About the Role:
In this role, you will design and deliver an automated ITIL Normal change process that integrates ServiceNow workflows with Azure DevOps pipelines. You’ll work closely with ITSM, DevOps and delivery teams to define risk-based approvals, automated scheduling, deployment triggers and outcome tracking.
You’ll also play a key role in updating supporting policies, procedures and technical documentation, as well as advocating for automation in change-averse environments.

What You’ll Be Doing

Designing and implementing workflows, integrations and business logic in ServiceNow
Integrating ServiceNow DevOps Change Velocity with Azure DevOps pipelines
Defining risk-based approval logic, automated scheduling and deployment triggers
Ensuring deployment outcomes (success/failure/review) are accurately captured in ServiceNow
Customising Azure DevOps Test Plans to support risk-based decision logic
Contributing to policy and procedure updates for the automated change process
Working with technical and business stakeholders to drive automation adoption
Producing clear documentation, including solution intent, workflows and risk considerations
What We’re Looking For
Strong hands-on experience with ServiceNow, ideally DevOps Change Velocity
Practical understanding of ITIL Change Management and automation opportunities
Experience with Azure DevOps pipelines and test plan customisation
Proven ability to design scalable, sustainable end-to-end solutions
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Ability to influence in complex or change-resistant environments
Strong documentation and design skills (workflows, business logic, risks)
Why You’ll Love This Role
Work at the forefront of ITSM and DevOps automation
Influence enterprise-wide change and delivery practices
Hybrid & flexible working options
Supportive, collaborative team environment
Opportunity to lead meaningful, high-impact solution design work

Anyone applying for this role must already have an AGSVA Security Clearance. 

Should you have any questions, feel free to reach out to Janice at janice.han@mtpservices.com.au

Ad Text:
Company Description

We reduce complexity and cost by delivering enterprise-grade data and AI platforms and solutions with minimal overhead – enabling smarter operations and insights without the cost and burden of fragmented systems.   

We help organisations understand, govern and protect their data through transparency on where it lives, how it’s used. We help them manage privacy, security and regulatory obligations – through tools that improve visibility on data assets, track lineage, enable data classification, policy enforcement and responsible data sharing.   

Job Description

We are seeking an experienced Data Platform Architect with deep expertise in the Microsoft cloud technology stack to join our professional services team. This role involves designing, building, and delivering scalable, secure, and high-performing data platforms for our clients using Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, and other modern data technologies. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in data platform architecture, solution design, and client delivery. 

Your Opportunity 

As a member of our Technology, Applications & Systems Integration team, the Data Platform Architect will: 

Lead the architecture, design, and implementation of enterprise data platforms for clients using Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, Azure Data Services, and related technologies. 

Develop end-to-end data solutions, including data ingestion, transformation, storage, and visualization layers. 

Collaborate with clients to gather requirements, assess current data environments, and define data strategies and roadmaps. 

Ensure solutions align with industry best practices, security standards, and compliance requirements. 

Provide technical leadership and mentorship to development teams and junior architects. 

Create and deliver architectural documentation, design patterns, and technical artifacts. 

Support the development of data governance frameworks and strategies for data quality, lineage, and access management. 

Drive performance optimization, scalability, and reliability in data platform architectures. 

Engage in pre-sales activities, contributing to solution proposals, effort estimation, and technical presentations. 

How are you extraordinary: 

You have excellent communication and stakeholder management skills. 

You are able to manage multiple programs for work simultaneously and have commercial experience with proposing new services and solutions 

You also have a demonstrated ability to lead technical workshops and engage with both technical and business audiences. 

You have strong problem-solving and analytical skill and an ability to produce high-quality documentation including written and diagrammatic for proposals, presentations and project artefacts. 

You are a collaborative team player with a consulting mindset. 

Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Information Systems, or similar considered favourably

Extensive experience designing and implementing data platforms on the Microsoft cloud stack (Azure Synapse Analytics, Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory, Azure SQL, Power BI, etc.). 

Strong expertise in data architecture patterns, including data lakes, data warehouses, lakehouses, and real-time data processing. 

Proficiency in modern data engineering tools and techniques, including ELT/ETL, data pipelines, and orchestration tools. 

Solid understanding of data modelling, data governance, and data security best practices. 

Experience working in a systems integrator or professional services environment, delivering client-facing solutions. 

Strong proficiency in programming and scripting languages like SQL, Python, and Spark. 

Microsoft certifications (e.g., Azure Solutions Architect Expert, Azure Data Engineer Associate) are highly desirable. 

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Group Description: We are seeking a detail-oriented and collaborative Strategy Technology Business Analyst to support the development and implementation of AI/ML and Generative AI solutions. The ideal candidate will act as a bridge between business and technical teams, ensuring that AI initiatives align with organizational goals and deliver tangible value. This role requires the ability to understand complex engineering concepts, communicate effectively with stakeholders, and manage standard Business Analyst responsibilities. We are looking for candidates with approximately 3-4 years of professional experience.







Project Description:

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather, analyze, and document business requirements for AI/ML and Generative AI initiatives.

Bridge the gap between business and technical teams by understanding and articulating complex engineering concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Conduct research and market analysis on AI/ML trends to support strategy development and identify opportunities for innovation.

Develop and maintain detailed project documentation, including business cases, process flows, and functional specifications.

Support the delivery of AI/ML solutions, ensuring alignment with business objectives, timelines, and best practices.







Key Skills: 

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate business needs into technical requirements.

Foundational understanding of AI/ML and Generative AI concepts, with the ability to engage in detailed engineering discussions.

Proficiency in documentation tools and techniques, such as process modeling and requirement traceability.

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, capable of facilitating collaboration between technical and non-technical teams.

Familiarity with cloud AI platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure) and AI/ML implementation frameworks is a plus.







Location: Sydney or Melbourne or Brisbane


Salary Range: $84,000 - $92,000 AUD




Benefits of working at Accenture:




·       18 weeks paid parental leave

·       Long & short-term career break opportunities

·       Structured career development program

·       Local and international career opportunities.

·       Certified as a Family Inclusive Workplace™

·       Flexible Work Arrangements - centered around Accenture’s Truly Human ethos and our commitment to supporting the health and wellbeing of our people.

·       We are proud to be in the top 3 of last year’s Diversity & Inclusion Index!

Job Title: Systems Engineer- Redhat, Elastic, Kubernetes- Major Bank-
Ad Text:
A major bank in Sydney is seeking an Observability Engineer for a new next-generation Elastic Enterprise Platform. This is a permanent role.
The role is paying $170k + super + 15k bonus.

Responsibilities:

Build, implement, and maintain enterprise-grade Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) environments.
Build, deploy, and support OpenShift and Kubernetes clusters for high-availability workloads.
Integrate and optimize Elasticsearch clusters within the new Elastic Enterprise Platform.
Key Skills / Experience:

3+ years of experience in Linux Redhat systems engineering and administration,
Experience with OpenShift and/or Kubernetes in production environments.
Familiarity with Elasticsearch or the Elastic Stack- not essential but preferred
Experience with automation tools
If interested please respond ASAP with your latest resume

Job Title: Genesys Cloud AI Forward Deployed Engineer
Ad Text:
Genesys empowers organizations of all sizes to improve loyalty and business outcomes by creating the best experiences for their customers and employees. Through Genesys Cloud, the AI-powered Experience Orchestration platform, organizations can accelerate growth by delivering empathetic, personalized experiences at scale to drive customer loyalty, workforce engagement, efficiency and operational improvements.

We employ more than 6,000 people across the globe who embrace empathy and cultivate collaboration to succeed. And, while we offer great benefits and perks like larger tech companies, our employees have the independence to make a larger impact on the company and take ownership of their work. Join the team and create the future of customer experience together.

Genesys Cloud AI Forward Deployed Engineer - Australia or New Zealand

This role opens up opportunities for candidates based in Australia or New Zealand.

As a Forward Deployed Engineer at Genesys, you will serve as the strategic and technical bridge between customer ambition and successful AI transformation.

You will partner directly with strategic customers across the Asia-Pacific region to design, prototype, and operationalise Genesys AI solutions that drive measurable improvements in customer experience and business performance. At Genesys, we’re transforming how organisations connect with their customers through empathy, collaboration, and innovation.

This role offers the opportunity to make a lasting impact by helping enterprises move from AI exploration to continuous transformation.

What You’ll Do

Discovery and Strategy Alignment

Partner with Genesys CX Advisors, Solution Consultants, and customer stakeholders to identify AI use cases aligned with strategic objectives.

Assess value, effort, and feasibility to prioritize initiatives effectively.

Translate customer KPIs (AHT, CSAT, containment rates, etc.) into actionable AI solution opportunities.

Design and Architecture

Define reference architectures, integration patterns, and data flows for AI-powered experience orchestration.

Lead process-redesign workshops to create seamless, channel-agnostic CX.

Ensure all designs comply with Genesys and customer security, privacy, and regulatory requirements (GDPR, PDPA, PCI, HIPAA where applicable).

Prototype and Implementation

Deliver rapid POC and MVP implementations using Genesys Cloud AI Studio, Copilot, and related product suites.

Integrate Genesys AI components with customer CRM, ERP, and third-party systems.

Establish implementation KPIs and analytics to measure model and journey performance.

Optimization and Continuous Improvement

Evaluate solution performance against KPIs and refine designs based on data-driven insights.

Collaborate with Customer Success and Professional Services teams to hand over production-ready assets and roadmaps.

Document best practices and reusable accelerators to strengthen future deployments.

Governance, Ethics, and Enablement

Champion responsible AI design principles and apply guardrails to prevent bias or unsafe responses.

Adhere to Genesys ethical standards and compliance frameworks.

Mentor customer and partner teams to build long-term AI maturity and self-sufficiency.

What We’re Looking For

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business, Data Science, or a related discipline, or equivalent hands-on experience in CX or AI solution delivery.

At least five years of experience implementing or supporting CX, CRM, or AI orchestration platforms (e.g., Genesys Cloud, Google CCAI, Salesforce, Microsoft, NICE CXone, AWS Connect, ServiceNow, or similar).

Three or more years of experience in solution architecture, systems integration, or AI/ML-enabled process design.

Demonstrated experience working with APIs, data pipelines, and modern cloud environments (Genesys, AWS, Azure, GCP).

Technical Skills

CX orchestration and workflow design across multiple platforms.

Conversational AI or Agent Assist implementation (voice, chat, messaging).

Data and integration expertise (REST APIs, event-driven architecture, JSON).

Understanding of cloud infrastructure and microservices.

Experience with reporting and analytics tools (SQL, Tableau, Power BI, or similar).

Familiarity with data governance and security compliance.

Knowledge of customer journey mapping and omnichannel CX processes.

Business and Soft Skills

Strong analytical and critical thinking; able to bridge technical and business domains.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement; able to build strong partnerships & confidence across business and technical teams to articulate and align solutions with strategic objectives.

Strong leadership in cross-functional environments; comfortable guiding customers through complexity and influencing executive stakeholders on AI adoption strategy.

Familiarity with industry verticals such as Insurance, Healthcare, Banking, Retail, or Public Sector.

Mentors peers and contributes to capability development across teams and partners.

Please note: Genesys will not accept resumes from agencies for this role.

To be eligible to apply for this role you must have work rights in Australia or New Zealand.

If a Genesys employee referred you, please use the link they sent you to apply.

About Genesys:

Genesys® empowers more than 8,000 organizations worldwide to create the best customer and employee experiences. With agentic AI at its core, Genesys Cloud™ is the AI-Powered Experience Orchestration platform that connects people, systems, data and AI across the enterprise. As a result, organizations can drive customer loyalty, growth and retention while increasing operational efficiency and teamwork across human and AI workforces. To learn more, visit www.genesys.com.

Reasonable Accommodations:

If you require a reasonable accommodation to complete any part of the application process, or are limited in your ability to access or use this online application and need an alternative method for applying, you or someone you know may contact us at reasonable.accommodations@genesys.com.

You can expect a response within 24–48 hours. To help us provide the best support, click the email link above to open a pre-filled message and complete the requested information before sending. If you have any questions, please include them in your email.

This email is intended to support job seekers requesting accommodations. Messages unrelated to accommodation—such as application follow-ups or resume submissions—may not receive a response.

Genesys is an equal opportunity employer committed to fairness in the workplace. We evaluate qualified applicants without regard to race, color, age, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, domestic partner status, national origin, genetics, disability, military and veteran status, and other protected characteristics.

Company description:



Join us and let's make a bigger difference together.

Established in 1840, we're Australia's first member-owned wellbeing company. Today we have over $1 billion in revenue and provide smart solutions and services to more than 700,000 Australians. We employ over 7000 people and our purpose is to Help People to Thrive.

It's an exciting time to be joining Australian Unity - we have grown significantly over recent years and are transforming to capitalise on further growth opportunities to help our customers and employees thrive. We operate with commercial principles and with a strong social purpose to create community value. Australian Unity is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.



Job description:



The primary objective of this critical role is to accelerate AI adoption at Australian Unity by leading end-to-end AI initiatives within the People & Culture (P&C) Business. This includes identifying and prioritising high-value use cases with stakeholders, selecting the most effective technologies or vendors, implementing and delivering solutions on time, and ensuring strong adoption to realise measurable business value.

Solutions will often be delivered by leveraging vendor solutions and low-code development platforms, requiring the AI Enablement Engineer to combine business engagement, vendor coordination, and low-code development skills to achieve outcomes. Responsibilities span the full AI lifecycle: discovery, design, low-code development, delivery, governance, change management, and post-deployment support.

In addition, the role contributes to enterprise-wide strategic AI initiatives, with the opportunity to specialise in one or more of three areas: AI Literacy & Change Management, AI Governance, or AI Innovation Process Optimisation, shaping our Enterprise AI Framework / Target State Architecture in the specialisation area. The role may also contribute to mentoring juniors, citizen-developers, and AI Ambassadors.

Mastering first-principles thinking will be critical to success in this role—challenging assumptions, breaking problems down to fundamentals, and designing AI solutions that directly address core business needs, while also providing thought leadership in enterprise-wide strategic AI initiatives. By applying this approach, the AI Enablement Engineer will shape both domain-level delivery and help drive Australian Unity's journey to becoming an AI-native organisation.

Accountabilities include:

End-to-end ownership of AI adoption within a business platform squad, from identifying opportunities, facilitating prioritisation and planning, solution selection, design and delivery, managing user uptake and value realisation, and supporting solutions post-deployment.
Deliver AI initiatives that build user confidence, simplify adoption, and realise tangible business value.
Ensure end-to-end delivery of AI projects—primarily leveraging vendor-provided solutions and low-code platforms—by aligning with Australian Unity's AI Governance Procedures and actively collaborating with cross-functional teams and stakeholders.
Apply AI governance frameworks, guardrails, and risk/compliance standards consistently across project design and delivery.
Ensure all solutions are robust, well-documented, and aligned with enterprise standards
Provide specialist expertise, define enterprise-level AI frameworks / target state architecture in at least one of AI literacy & change management, AI governance or AIOps process optimization

About You:

To be successful in the role you will be able to demonstrate the following capabilities / experience:

Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Science, Business, or other fields relevant to the role
Substantial professional experience (5+ years), including demonstrated success in consulting, business-facing, or technology enablement roles. Experience within industries such as health, insurance, banking, or wealth & capital markets is desirable.
Demonstrated experience in technology solution enablement — including opportunity identification, vendor onboarding, low-code prototyping, solution design, delivery coordination, and change adoption.
Strong communication skills and able to tailor complex AI/ML concenpts for non-technical audiences and influence decisions across business and technology.
Exposure to or contribution towards initiatives in one or more areas of AI Literacy & Change Management, AIOps / MLOps / LLMOp
Hands-on experience with low-code and automation platforms e.g., Microsoft Power Automate, Copilot Studio (desirable)
Familiarity with governance and compliance frameworks related to AI, data privacy, and ethical AI (desirable)

What's on Offer:

You will enjoy a range of great employee benefits and rewards including:

Competitive salary + bonus program
Enjoy additional yearly Well-Being and Community leave days
14-week paid parental leave, with equal benefit for both parents
Employee Referral Program
Employee Assistance Program - support and assistance for you and your partner at those times in life when you need it most
Maxxia Rewards - a great range of discounts and benefits at selected retail outlets, department stores, attractions, travel, cinemas, restaurants.
Discounts across the Australian Unity business including Private Health Insurance, General Insurance + more!
Available access to LinkedIn Learning courses through our great Learning platform

For further benefits visit: https://www.australianunity.com.au/careers/culture

Australian Unity is an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from all members of the community, including people of Aboriginal and Torres strait Islander descent, culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and, mature aged people.

Job Title: Software Engineer, Android Laptops and Tablets, Early Career
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience.
1 year of experience with software development in one or more programming languages (e.g., Java, Kotlin, Python, C, C++).
Preferred qualifications:

Master's degree in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or a related technical field.
1 year of experience in developing Android applications or Android OS.
Experience with general AI and Machine Learning methods.
Experience in working collaboratively on complex projects.
Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
About the job


Google's software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how billions of users connect, explore, and interact with information and one another. Our products need to handle information at massive scale, and extend well beyond web search. We're looking for engineers who bring fresh ideas from all areas, including information retrieval, distributed computing, large-scale system design, networking and data storage, security, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, UI design and mobile; the list goes on and is growing every day. As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.

With your technical expertise, you will manage project priorities, deadlines, and deliverables. You will design, develop, test, deploy, maintain, and enhance software solutions.

Android is Google’s open-source mobile operating system powering more than 3 billion devices worldwide. Android is about bringing computing to everyone in the world. We believe computing is a super power for good, enabling access to information, economic opportunity, productivity, connectivity between friends and family and more. We think everyone in the world should have access to the best computing has to offer. We provide the platform for original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and developers to build compelling computing devices (smartphones, tablets, TVs, wearables, etc) that run the best apps/services for everyone in the world.

Responsibilities

Deliver innovative AI and intelligent features in Android, focusing on end-to-end experiences from front-end development to advanced modeling and back-end implementation.
Work on client integration, including OS-level integration, API development, lifecycle management, and back-end communication.
Collaborate with other team members and our product team to scope, plan, design and launch new features in the Intelligent System Experiences team across Android.
Work with AI/ML partner teams across Android to help them integrate their features.
Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.

Sydney-based start-up with significant media attention, founders gathering to go for round 3, after previous successful exits. 

What you need to have done already:

Shipped high-traffic backend services (Python, TS, Go, Rust — whatever you’re good at) that don’t fall over
Designed and owned the whole AI stack end-to-end: LLM inference, RAG pipelines, eval systems, agent tooling, vector DBs, observability
Taken LLM serving + tooling from zero to handling serious load yourself (not just demos)
Profound, practical knowledge of RAG, agents, evals, prompting, tracing, the stuff that actually matters when things are live
Prove you can move fast without breaking everything
Small team, considerable scope, proper funding. This is a genuine founding engineer position; you’ll own significant chunks of the core product.
If you’re currently stuck working on boring enterprise junk or prompt-wrangling at a place that never ships real volume, hit me up.

Contact: Jason@blackroc.co

Job Title: Support System Design Engineering Project Manager
Ad Text:
About us:

At Lockheed Martin Australia, we believe that when people are empowered, inspired, and supported, they can achieve extraordinary things. We embrace flexibility, so our people can be their best inside and outside of work. We champion inclusion and continuous learning, ensuring all voices are heard and valued. And we thrive on collaboration, turning challenges into opportunities for growth and innovation.  As a leader in national security, our innovative and diverse programs create a more secure future for Australia across space, air, land, sea, and cyber domains. Every day is a chance to solve the world’s most complex challenges and make a profound impact. Experience it here.

About the Program:

AIR6500 is the RAAF’s $3 billion program to develop a joint air battle management system that builds on the capabilities offered by Next Generation sensor and command and control systems. AIR6500 will create a fully networked ‘system of systems’ that synchronises air and missile defence operations in joint and coalition environments, maximising situational awareness and enhancing the speed of decision making across the battlespace.

About the role:

The Support System Design Engineering Project Manager (EPM) is responsible for the technical management of the Operational Continuity Integrated Product Team (IPT) and for leading it through all phases of the product lifecycle from development and production to delivery and sustainment.

The EPM is accountable for overall program performance, ensuring the team meets its technical, cost, schedule, and quality objectives, while effectively managing risks and opportunities. Acting as the primary point of communication for the IPT, the EPM coordinates with functional areas, allocates tasks, and provides performance feedback to support successful program execution.

Day to day responsibilities:

Define and document the team’s operating approach, including roles, responsibilities, communication protocols, and decision-making processes.

Plan, schedule, and facilitate regular team meetings to drive effective communication, collaboration, and progress toward program objectives.

Clearly assign and communicate tasks and responsibilities to team members, ensuring clarity of expectations and accountability.

Develop and maintain a detailed project schedule outlining key milestones, deadlines, and deliverables to ensure alignment with program requirements.

Collaborate with functional areas — including engineering, manufacturing, and logistics — to secure the necessary resources and expertise for successful execution.

Prepare and deliver regular status reports and updates to stakeholders, including program managers, customers, and senior leadership, ensuring transparency of progress, risks, and issues.

Proactively identify, manage, and mitigate risks and issues that may affect team performance or program outcomes.

Drive continuous improvement by identifying and implementing process enhancements that improve team efficiency and productivity.

Monitor, manage, and report on team performance metrics, tracking progress against defined goals and objectives.

About you:

Extensive experience in communicating, coordinating, prioritising, and monitoring work progress to achieve defined goals.

Proven success in leading and managing multi-disciplinary product teams within complex project environments.

Strong problem-solving skills, with the ability to identify and resolve impediments, manage conflicts, and prioritise competing outcomes.

Highly advanced knowledge of Agile frameworks, processes, and tools.

Demonstrated experience in assessing capability needs, developing plans, and implementing skill improvement initiatives.

Experience in the definition, development, and delivery of Support Systems for Commonwealth programs.

Any skills in the following is highly desirable:

Experience in Systems Engineering practices and methodologies.

Background in Complex Systems Integration and Test.

Understanding of Model-Based Engineering processes.

SAFe (Scaled Agile Framework) training or certification.

Experience in Control Account Management

How we reward and support you:

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else. We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

Flexible work & Hybrid work options

Access to our online discounts program offering immediate discounts or cashback

A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family  

Additional benefits such as Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs

Learning & Development platforms to encourage ongoing self-development 

Special requirements:

Applicants must be eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Defence Security Clearance and employment may be contingent on the provision of further personal information including citizenship to ensure compliance with international export control legislation and regulations. 

Employment may be contingent on the satisfactory result of criminal and/or other background screens, which require the collection and transfer of personal information.

Equal Opportunity Statement:

Lockheed Martin Australia supports Equal Employment Opportunity and values diversity in the workplace by creating a place of employment that is, free of unlawful discrimination and is harassment free, fair, ethical, inclusive, and values the contribution of all its employees. By leveraging our employees’ unique talents and experiences, we will deliver innovative, affordable solutions and unparalleled customer value.

As part of our endeavours to increase participation of Indigenous Australians, we welcome applications from all people, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.

We are committed to creating a workplace where everyone can thrive. If you are selected for this role, we would be happy to discuss any accommodations that will help you to be successful

A Veteran-friendly Workplace:

Veterans are encouraged to apply. We highly value the unique skills and experiences that veterans and transitioning service members can contribute to our team. We are proud to be recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer by the Australian Government.

Principal Architect – AI & Machine Learning

📍 Australia (Sydney preferred, hybrid) | 🌐 daisee.com

Australian work authorisation is required at the start of employment for this position.

daisee is a leading AI company building world-class solutions for speech analytics, conversation intelligence, and automated quality management.

We are expanding our team and looking for an Australia based Principal Architect to help shape the next generation of our AI-driven platform.

The Opportunity

As Principal Architect, you'll be at the heart of daisee's product evolution – guiding architectural strategy, bringing new ideas to life, and staying hands-on with modern AI tooling.

You'll balance technical depth with conceptual thinking, ensuring our solutions scale across global enterprises while maintaining the highest standards of quality, performance, and security.

What You'll Do

· Lead the architecture design for daisee's AI/ML-driven SaaS platform.

· Drive architectural decisions across data infrastructure, ML pipelines, and scalable AWS cloud systems.

· Influence the technical direction of multiple product teams and be a go-to escalation point for complex technical issues.

· Promote best practices in coding, architecture, and system design to ensure maintainability, scalability, and performance.

· Guide engineering teams to make the right trade-offs between speed, quality, and business needs.

· Research, evaluate, and recommend emerging technologies, tools, and methodologies to enhance daisee's engineering capability.

· Collaborate across product, engineering, and business stakeholders to deliver high-impact solutions.

· Lead and contribute to technical discussions that drive alignment and better outcomes.

Our purpose

Here at Datacom we connect people and technology in order to solve challenges, create opportunities and discover new possibilities for the communities we live in

About the Role (your why)

The way we work and our customer needs are changing! We are going through a significant AI uplift that will be a real game changer in the ANZ Market. Our customers are loving our story and excited about our new service solutions. As such we are seeking a Senior/Tech lead developers who want to get on board our journey. We need someone who is passionate about AI development and wants to push boundaries. Your software background is key but your passion for AI is a must. This role will see you will join our Digital Engineering team, focusing on delivering innovative AI-driven software solutions. We will offer you opportunity to work on cutting-edge projects, collaborating with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and use the latest AI Models that address complex business challenges. We need multiple people but we need them now so please don't hesitate this is your chance to put an ANZ company on the global map!!!

What you’ll bring

Must-haves

7+ years professional software development (Python and Typescript preferred) with production ML/AI experience
Demonstrated delivery of at least one generative-AI solution in production (chatbot, summariser, code assistant, etc.)
Deep familiarity with transformers and orchestration stacks such as LangChain v0.2+, LlamaIndex or Semantic Kernel
Practical experience deploying or fine-tuning models on Azure OpenAI / AI Foundry or AWS Bedrock / SageMaker
Hands-on with RAG patterns, vector databases and evaluation metrics (BLEU, ROUGE-L, GPTScore)
Cloud-native engineering skills: Docker, Kubernetes (AKS/EKS), infra-as-code and automated testing

Nice-to-haves

Agent frameworks (AutoGen 0.2/0.4, CrewAI) and tool-using agents. 
Multimodal model workflows (image-text with GPT-4o, Gpt4o real time API).
Experience with embedding models
Workspace automation using agentic frameworks
Advanced RAG variants – familiarity with LongRAG, Self-RAG, GraphRAG and the trade-offs between leading vector stores (Pinecone, Qdrant, FAISS, Azure AI Search)
Multimodal & streaming LLMs – delivering real-time GPT-4o or Gemini 2 Ultra use-cases (image to text or speech) and cross-modal embeddings.

Why join us here at Datacom?

Datacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It's our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.

We care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.

We operate at the forefront of technology to help Australia and New Zealand’s largest enterprise organisations explore possibilities and solve their greatest challenges, so you will never run out of interesting new challenges and opportunities.

We want Datacom to be an inclusive and welcoming workplace for everyone and take pride in the steps we have taken and continue to take to make our environment fun and friendly, and our people feel supported.
